value.value: A scoring system for graft versus host disease that combines a score for percentage of body surface area (BSA) involved with a score for disease signs and cutaneous features.
Body surface area involvement is 0 percent and there are no sclerotic features.
Body surface area involvement is 1-18 percent.
Body surface area involvement is 19-50 percent and there are superficial sclerotic features.

Body surface area involvement is greater than 50 percent and there are any skin features that are Score 3. This score is also used when superficial sclerotic features are present (Score 2), but there is impaired mobility or ulceration (Score 3).

Tissue composed of one or more layers of epithelial cells and a basement membrane. It lines the secretory alveoli and secretory ducts of the prostate. The secretory epithelium consists mostly of pseudostratified columnar cells and basal cells with areas of cuboidal and squamous epithelial cells. The walls of the prostatic urethra and the distal regions of the longer ducts are lined with transitional epithelium.
Hyperinsulinism that resolves spontaneously. This is the most common cause of neonatal hypoglycemia.
Reduced concentration of thyroid hormone(s), usually associated with a non-thyroidal illness, that resolves spontaneously.
Hyperparathyroidism in an infant less than one month of age that resolves spontaneously.

label.value: GvHD Body Surface Area Involvement Score

value.value: A score for graft versus host disease based on the percentage of of body surface area (BSA) involved.
Primary hypothyroidism that resolves spontaneously.
No body surface area involved.
1-18% of body surface area involved.
19-50% of body surface area involved.
Greater than 50% of body surface area involved.
A score for graft versus host disease based on features of skin involvement.

The non-glandular tissue of the prostate gland, consisting of two major cell types, smooth muscle cells and fibroblasts. Stromal cells are key regulators of growth and differentiation in the prostate.
No sclerotic features.
Superficial sclerotic features; not hidebound (able to pinch).
One or more of: deep sclerotic features; hidebound; impaired mobility; ulceration.
A scoring system for graft versus host disease that combines a symptoms score with a score for FEV1.
FEV1 is greater than or equal to 80 percent with or without lung symptoms.
FEV1 is 60 to 79 percent and lung symptoms are none or mild.
Reduced response to thyroid stimulating hormone resulting in low thyroid hormone production despite elevated thyroid stimulating hormone, associated with mutation(s) in the TSHR gene.
FEV1 is 40 to 59 percent and lung symptoms are none to moderate.
FEV1 is less than or equal to 39 percent and lung symptoms are none to severe.
A score for graft versus host disease based on the severity of lung symptoms.
No symptoms.
Mild symptoms (shortness of breath after climbing one flight of steps).
Moderate symptoms (shortness of breath after walking on flat ground).
Severe symptoms (shortness of breath at rest; requiring O2).
A score for graft versus host disease based on FEV1.
FEV1 greater than or equal to 80%.
FEV1 less than or equal to 39%.
Familial glucocorticoid deficiency caused by mutation(s) in the TXNRD2 gene encoding thioredoxin reductase 2.

A ridge of urothelium in the prostatic urethra that serves as an important anatomical landmark that is important in the classification of several urethral disorders, including posterior urethral valves, urethral carcinoid tumors, and hypospadias.
Any type of immunotherapy that targets and blocks the immune checkpoint pathways to activate immune responses against tumor cells.
Indicates that MYC expression has been detected in a sample.
Indicates that MYCN expression has been detected in a sample.
Indicates that CD5 expression has been detected in a sample.
A cytogenetic finding indicating that the translocation t(11;14) has not been detected in a sample.
A molecular abnormality indicating the presence of an abnormally high level of the ephrin type-A receptor 2 protein.
Indicates that CD22 expression has been detected in a sample.
Indicates that expression of the BCR/ABL1 fusion protein has not been detected in a sample.
Indicates that MET expression has been detected in a sample.
Indicates that the expression of a RET fusion has been detected in a sample.
A layer of epithelium comprising both columnar and small cuboidal cells.
Indicates that the expression of a NTRK1 fusion has been detected in a sample.
